## Task 4 ICMP: Troubleshooting Networks

Purpose: Diagnostics and error reporting.
Commands:
- Ping: ICMP Echo Request (Type 8) → Echo Reply (Type 0). Measures RTT, packet loss.
- Traceroute/Tracert: Uses TTL field; routers decrement TTL, send ICMP Time Exceeded (Type 11).
Ping Example
Code
ping 192.168.11.1 -c 4
64 bytes from 192.168.11.1: icmp_seq=1 ttl=63 time=11.2 ms
...
-4 packets transmitted, 4 received, 0% packet loss
rtt min/avg/max/mdev = 3.805/10.596/23.366/7.956 ms
Shows connectivity, RTT statistics, and packet loss.
Traceroute Example
Code
traceroute example.com
1  _gateway (192.168.66.1)
2  192.168.11.1
...
16  93.184.215.14 (example.com)
Reveals routers along the path.
Some routers don’t respond (* * *).
Routes may change dynamically.

